type: web_research
title: fal.ai Video Generation API - Complete Research for Japanese VSL
source: "https://fal.ai, https://docs.fal.ai, various fal.ai model pages"
key_insights[15]: "fal.ai offers 600+ models including 40+ video generation models from Kling, Veo, Wan, Sora, Seedance, PixVerse, Hailuo, Luma, etc.",Most models generate 3-15 second clips maximum; 25s max for Sora 2 Pro,"For longer videos (14-35s per scene), must stitch multiple short clips using fal-ai/ffmpeg-api/merge-videos","Wan 2.6 is cheapest at ~$0.05-0.15/sec with I2V supporting 5/10/15s durations and 9:16 vertical","Kling 3.0 supports 3-15s, multi-shot up to 6 shots, custom elements, native audio, 9:16 vertical at $0.168-0.308/sec","Veo 3.1 supports 4/6/8s, 720p-4K, 9:16 vertical at $0.20-0.60/sec",Sora 2 supports up to 25s with audio at $0.30-0.50/sec,"PixVerse has native anime/comic/3d_animation style presets, cheapest for anime at $0.15-0.40/video","Hailuo 2.3 expanded anime/illustration/ink painting/game CG style support, $0.50/video","Rate limits: 2 concurrent tasks default, 40 with $1000+ credits","Authentication via FAL_KEY environment variable, Queue API at queue.fal.run","Output format is MP4, all models support aspect_ratio 9:16 for vertical video","Image-to-video is the recommended approach for VSL: generate 4K images first, then animate with I2V models",LongCat Video by Meituan specifically designed for temporal consistency in longer sequences,Seedance 1.5 Pro has dual-branch audio-video simultaneous generation with lip-sync
findings[10]: "Best anime/manga models: PixVerse (native anime preset), Hailuo 2.3 (anime/illustration), Wan 2.2 (stylization prompts)","Best photorealistic: Kling 3.0 Pro, Veo 3.1, Sora 2","Best cost-efficiency: Wan 2.6 ($0.05/sec), PixVerse ($0.15-0.20/video for 5s)","Best quality: Veo 3.1, Kling 3.0 Pro, Sora 2 Pro","Best for Ken Burns/subtle animation: Any I2V model with camera movement prompts","FFmpeg API available for video stitching: fal-ai/ffmpeg-api/merge-videos",No model has specific Japanese language support - prompts in English recommended,"All major models support 9:16 vertical format for mobile/VSL content",Multi-shot in Kling 3.0 allows up to 6 shots with consistent characters,Veo 3.1 extend-video can extend up to 30s total
techniques:
  authentication: "Set FAL_KEY env var, use Authorization: Key $FAL_KEY header"
  queue_api: "POST queue.fal.run/{model_id}, poll status, get result"
  subscribe: "fal.subscribe(model_id, {input: {...}}) - auto-handles queue"
  video_stitching: fal-ai/ffmpeg-api/merge-videos to concatenate clips
  vertical_video: "Set aspect_ratio: '9:16' or use 9:16 input image for I2V"
  anime_style: "PixVerse style:'anime', Hailuo prompt-based, Wan stylization keywords"
  extend_video: Veo 3.1 extend-video endpoint can extend up to 30s
refs[9]: "wan/v2.6/image-to-video - Wan 2.6 I2V endpoint, 5/10/15s, 480p-1080p","fal-ai/kling-video/v3/standard/image-to-video - Kling 3.0 Standard I2V, 3-15s","fal-ai/veo3.1/image-to-video - Veo 3.1 I2V, 4/6/8s, up to 4K","fal-ai/sora-2/text-to-video/pro - Sora 2 Pro T2V, up to 25s",fal-ai/pixverse/v4.5/image-to-video - PixVerse I2V with anime preset,fal-ai/minimax/hailuo-2.3-fast/pro/image-to-video - Hailuo 2.3 I2V anime support,fal-ai/bytedance/seedance/v1.5/pro/text-to-video - Seedance 1.5 with audio sync,fal-ai/ffmpeg-api/merge-videos - Video concatenation,fal-ai/ffmpeg-api/merge-audio-video - Audio-video merge
recommendations[7]: "For VSL with 20 scenes at 14-35s each: Use image-to-video approach with existing 4K images","Primary recommendation: Wan 2.6 I2V for cost-efficiency, PixVerse for anime style, Kling 3.0 for quality","Strategy for 14-35s scenes: Generate 3-7 clips of 5s each per scene, stitch with ffmpeg-api",Use Kling 3.0 multi-shot for scenes needing character consistency across multiple shots,"For Ken Burns/illustration animation: Use camera movement prompts like 'slow dolly zoom', 'pan left'","Budget estimate for 20 scenes at ~20s avg: Wan=$20, PixVerse=$16-40, Kling=$67-123, Veo=$80-160","Start with Wan 2.6 or PixVerse for testing, upgrade to Kling/Veo for final production"
